menu "bb_display_st77xx"

choice BB_DISPLAY_ST77XX_VARIANT
    prompt "ST77xx panel variant"
    default BB_DISPLAY_ST77XX_VARIANT_ST7735
    help
        Picks which backend the bb_display_st77xx component compiles
        and registers. Both variants share the underlying ESP-IDF
        st7789 panel driver; the ST7735 path overlays a custom
        vendor-init sequence (gamma/power/frame) needed for the
        LilyGo T-Dongle S3 panel that the default ST7735 driver
        doesn't program correctly. Future probe-capable boards can
        register both and let the registry's probe()->init() walker
        pick at runtime.

config BB_DISPLAY_ST77XX_VARIANT_ST7735
    bool "ST7735 (LilyGo T-Dongle S3)"

config BB_DISPLAY_ST77XX_VARIANT_ST7789
    bool "ST7789 (generic)"

endchoice

config BB_DISPLAY_ST7735_SKIP_VENDOR_INIT
    bool "ST7735: skip vendor-init overlay"
    depends on BB_DISPLAY_ST77XX_VARIANT_ST7735
    default n
    help
        The ST7735 backend overlays a custom vendor-init sequence
        (gamma/power/frame) on top of esp_lcd_new_panel_st7789's
        standard init. This is needed for the LilyGo T-Dongle S3
        panel, where the default driver doesn't program the chip
        correctly. Enable this option for ST7735 panels where the
        stock driver works on its own — skips the overlay entirely.

endmenu
